The paper is close, but I would not mark the full manuscript dual-≥8 ready yet because the new backbone evidence is not propagated consistently.

The main regression is factual inconsistency across sections. `results.tex` now claims a full 3-backbone × 8-domain grid, but the Abstract, Conclusion, and Limitations still describe the older “Llama on four new winning domains” version. The Limitations section is especially problematic: it says you have not run the remaining four domains or a third model family, which is now false. That would immediately signal manuscript drift to a reviewer.

The 6/8 framing is otherwise strong and mostly honest. Beauty and Movies are repeatedly disclosed, the losses are quantified, and the uncertainty/risk decomposition is correctly framed as a negative result rather than the source of the gain. I also appreciate that the new robustness section preserves the loss partition instead of laundering the result through averages.

The remaining overclaim risk is in wording like “the advantage is not specific to Qwen3-8B.” Given baselines are held at unified-Qwen values while only C-CRP’s scorer is swapped, the safer claim is: “the C-CRP posterior remains competitive under frozen-model substitution.” The new section says this caveat, but the Conclusion currently does not.

As a top-conference reviewer, I would score the scientific package around 8 once synchronized, but the submitted paper as shown is not clean enough because core sections disagree about a headline robustness result.

SCORE_PONY_PAPER: 7.6/10

Single most important fix: update Abstract, Conclusion, and Limitations to match the full 3-backbone × 8-domain robustness result, while preserving the caveat that only C-CRP’s scoring backbone was swapped and the baselines remain the unified-Qwen comparison rows.
